{
  "name": "RPlog_Culture_on_Myrkr",
  "title": "Culture on Myrkr",
  "summary": "In the cleared area before the main house at Karrde's hidden base on Myrkr, the Jedi Jessalyn returns sun-flushed from a swim and finds the mechanic Orson Tighe finishing repair work on the fleet's power nodes. Amid quiet, loaded references to the previous night and the still-unready Uwannabuyim, Jessalyn offers to resume teaching Orson the ways of the Force, and he accepts despite worries about complicating things with her and Simon. The former Imperial spymaster Declan Rahn joins them, reporting on the base's security and the slow progress of Karrde's plans, before Orson cheerfully drafts him into staging an opera, Two Standard Years, to bring some culture to the base. Declan's pointed commentary on Imperial propaganda glorifying Tarkin's death aboard the first Death Star strikes a raw nerve in Jessalyn, who quietly reveals she was a pilot on the rebel side at Yavin. She excuses herself to clean up, leaving Declan reflecting on the truth behind such propaganda.",
